> Ground beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

Please refer to the recipe card for Step 1.

== Patties ==

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @ground beef{10%ounce}, @ricotta cheese{4%ounce}, @parmesan cheese{1%ounce}, @artichoke hearts{1.25%ounce}, and @Italian herb & red pepper blend{3/4%tsp}.

Form the mixture into patties and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat @cooking oil{} in a #9.5-10-inch stainless steel pan{} over medium-high heat and pan sear the patties until browned on each side, about ~{3-5%minutes}.

Transfer the patties to a #baking sheet{} and top with a blend of ricotta, Parmesan, and artichokes. Broil until the meat is juicy and the topping is melty, about ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Cauliflower Rice ==

Heat @olive oil{} in a #large skillet{}. Add @kaale{2.75%ounce} and @roasted almonds{1/2%ounce}, cooking until kale is tender and almonds are toasted, about ~{5-7%minutes}.

Add @riced cauliflower{6.5%ounce} to the skillet and cook until heated through, about ~{3%minutes}.

Season cauliflower "rice" with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

== Sunflower Basil Sauce ==

Drizzle @sunflower basil sauce{2.25%ounce} over the patties and cauliflower rice for a pop of herby freshness.